The paper deals with joint optimization of artificial noise and information signals in a MIMO wiretap interference network, which involves information theory (cs.IT), game theory (cs.GT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.MM), and security and privacy (cs.SI). The paper proposes a nonconvex game approach to solve the optimization problem, which further supports the likelihood of these categories.
